    <h2>What it's for</h2>
    <p>The <strong>Stuff</strong> box type is the no-frills, get-things-done option. It strips away complexity and gives you a clean two-state system — <strong>Open</strong> or <strong>Closed</strong> — with a Kanban board as the primary view.</p>
    <p>Ideal for: personal to-do lists, household inventories, simple team backlogs, shopping lists, or any collection where you just need to track whether something is done or not.</p>

    <h2>Fields</h2>
    <table class="dtable">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Summary</strong></td><td>Text</td><td>What the item is</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Description</strong></td><td>Long Text</td><td>Optional notes or details</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Assignee</strong></td><td>User</td><td>Who is responsible</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>No extra fields — you can always add custom ones from Box Settings → Custom Fields.</p>

    <h2>Workflow</h2>
    <p>Stuff uses the simplest possible workflow:</p>
    <div class="wf-states">
      <div class="wf-state" style="--sc:#6366f1">Open</div>
      <div class="wf-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="wf-state" style="--sc:#22c55e">Closed</div>
    </div>
    <p>Items are <strong>Open</strong> until you mark them done. Closed items can be reopened at any time. The Kanban board renders one column per state.</p>

    <h2>Kanban view</h2>
    <p>Open the box to see your items arranged in columns by status. Drag a card from <strong>Open</strong> to <strong>Closed</strong> to complete it — no extra clicks required.</p>

    <div class="callout callout-tip">
      <i class="bi bi-stars"></i>
      <div>Make the box <strong>public</strong> to share a read-only view of your stuff with anyone — no login required.</div>
    </div>

    <h2>Tips</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Add a <strong>Priority</strong> select field to sort what to tackle first.</li>
      <li>Use <strong>relations</strong> to link related items — e.g. mark one item as blocking another.</li>
      <li>Filter the list view by assignee to see only your items in shared team boxes.</li>
    </ul>

